  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 10,
    "text": "Bake Sale"
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 11,
    "text": "One day, Mac and Tosh were reading, and Billy came along."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 12,
    "text": "Good Morning, Billy, Tosh said."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 13,
    "text": "You look upset, Mac said."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 14,
    "text": "My bike is broken! Billy said."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 15,
    "text": "Oh no! Tosh replied."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 16,
    "text": "I dont have enough money to get it fixed, Billy sighed."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 17,
    "text": "Tosh said, Mac, we must help Billy fix his bike."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 18,
    "text": "Dont be upset, Billy, I have an idea, Mac said."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 19,
    "text": "We can have a bake sale, he added."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 20,
    "text": "Mac started making signs."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 21,
    "text": "Mac put the signs up"
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 22,
    "text": "all over town."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 23,
    "text": "Tosh started picking apples and baking."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 24,
    "text": "Tosh baked many yummy apple treats."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 25,
    "text": "People bought apple pies."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 26,
    "text": "People bought applesauce."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 27,
    "text": "People bought apple jams."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 28,
    "text": "People bought apple tarts."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 29,
    "text": "Soon, they had enough money for Billy to fix his bike."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 30,
    "text": "Thanks, Mac and Tosh, Billy said."
  },
  {
    "page": 0,
    "index": 31,
    "text": "Apples rule! he added."
  }
]